The installed version is CGAL-0.901, i.e. the official 0.9 version with a 
few corrections made by stschirr@mpi-sb.mpg.de. Version 1.0 is coming soon!

CGAL documentation is available online through doc_html/index.html. Postscript
versions of the reference manual, a `getting started' document and a document on STL 
and CGAL are in doc_ps, printed versions are in a CGAL-folder in AG1's group 
library. 
The directory `examples' contains example programs. Especially, it contains a 
makefile. To compile with CGAL, you should include a CGAL_MAKEFILE designed for your
platform and wishes, and use the macros defined there. See examples/makefile
for an example. See the make/README for some info on the names of the available
makefiles.
There are name conflicts with STL and LEDA. To work around this you have to use 
some tricks, e.g. (un)prefix STL (you may, of course, prefer to maintain your own 
prefixed leda_version) by including CGAL/(un)prefix_stl.h. 
The g++-version uses the RTTI-feature, which affects the organization of class data.
Don't mix code compiled with and without that feature.

Enjoy CGAL and its flexibility!







